vipCitation.title: PharmGKB VIP Summary: MTHFR
vipCitation.notes: This document contains text that was found on the PharmGKB VIP page for MTHFR prior to Oct 2024.
vipSummary.html: Methylenetetrahydrofolate reductase (MTHFR) plays a key role in folate metabolism and is implicated in the pharmacodynamics of several drugs.

name: solute carrier family 19 member 1
chr.name: chr21
vipCitation.title: SLC19A1 pharmacogenomics summary.
vipSummary.html: SLC19A1 encodes the reduced folate carrier protein 1 (RFC1), a transporter protein. RFC1 is a high-capacity, bi-directional transporter of 5-methyl-tetrahydrofolate and thiamine monophosphate. It also actively transports antifolate chemotherapeutic agents, such as methotrexate (MTX), into cells.
vipCitation.authors: ['Yee Sook Wah', 'Gong Li', 'Badagnani Ilaria', 'Giacomini Kathleen M', 'Klein Teri E', 'Altman Russ B']

name: ATP binding cassette subfamily B member 1
chr.name: chr7
vipCitation.title: Very important pharmacogene summary: ABCB1 (MDR1, P-glycoprotein).
vipSummary.html: ABCB1, also known as multi-drug resistance protein 1 (MDRP1), is one of forty-nine putative members in the superfamily of human adenosine triphosphate (ATP)-binding cassette (ABC) transporters that encode transporter and channel proteins that function as efflux pumps.
